& [Inference] is bounded and restrained
  + [primary_observation] is the Lambda-Mellin unit is a coherent shared comparison unit because both rails can be measured as finite weighted Lambda contribution in Re(s) > 1
  + [identity_boundary] is the shared unit does not make explicit zero truncation and Euler prime-power cutoff the same identity
  + [diagnostic_result] is explicit psi estimates projected by raw finite differences create a stable-looking but non-shrinking bridge residual, so explicit-side projection error dominates the bridge
  + [window_observation] is lanczos is the best bridge window for sigma=2 samples, while sharp remains best for the harder sigma=1.5 first-zero-ordinate samples
  + [comparison_result] is the bridge is useful as an analysis primitive, but not stable enough to justify a stronger explicit/Euler bridge identity
  + [answered_question] is yes, a source-defined shared comparison unit can be created; no, this raw finite-difference bridge does not resolve the explicit/Euler boundary
  + [next_reasonable_coordinate] is if continued, source-define a smoother Stieltjes or partial-summation bridge before adding more windows or scale laws

  = must: treat Lambda-Mellin bridge traces as finite Re(s)>1 diagnostics only
  = must: preserve the distinction between exact finite Lambda cutoff residual and explicit-side projected Lambda residual
  = must: treat the plateau near 0.202 as a finite diagnostic observation, not a theorem signal
  = must: prefer smoothing or partial summation before any stronger explicit/Euler identity attempt
  - never: claim RH proof, disproof, independent zero certification, critical-line authority, universal bridge identity, or explicit/Euler fusion from this atlas

